T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 254
EP  - 260
VL  - 34
IS  - 2
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - This paper considers a bicriterion scheduling problem where a linear combination of two objective functions is considered, with weighting factors used to represent relative importance of the two criteria, i.e., total flowtime and range of lateness. A branch-and-bound solution procedure is designed for the problem. Computational results are also reported.
AB  - This paper considers a bicriterion scheduling problem where a linear combination of two objective functions is considered, with weighting factors used to represent relative importance of the two criteria, i.e., total flowtime and range of lateness. A branch-and-bound solution procedure is designed for the problem. Computational results are also reported.
